The paper discusses metrics for measuring scholarly impact, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. However, the focus on publications and citations suggests that cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely sub-category. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
